Action types:
- "navigate"  → go to URL (value = URL, target = null)
- "click"     → click an element (target = element description)
- "fill"      → type into an input (target = element, value = text to type)
- "select"    → pick from a dropdown (target = element, value = option text)
- "hover"     → hover over element (target = element)
- "press"     → keyboard press (target = element or null, value = key e.g. "Enter")
- "scroll"    → scroll page (value = "down" / "up" / "to_bottom")
- "wait"      → wait for condition (value = description of what to wait for)
- "assert"    → verify something (target = element, value = expected state/text)
- "extract"   → capture a value (target = element, value = what to extract)

Rules:
- Describe targets in plain English — they will be resolved to locators by another agent
- Each step must be atomic and executable in isolation
- If a value is not applicable for an action, set it to null
- Order steps exactly as they should be executed
